Led by Cory Redwine, Conservation Director of Project SeaSafe, this is the 4th Annual Clean Water Collective and it’s bigger than ever. This time, we’re in Grant, Florida, where 4 million clams are being released into the Indian River Lagoon, paired with the planting of thousands of mangroves, oyster work by CCA and trash clean ups to help restore one of Florida’s most critical ecosystems. But it’s not just about hard work—it’s about connection. With local captains, fishing legends, and the Local Knowledge crew on hand, we hit the water to show why this place is worth fighting for. From clam drops by drone, to in-water mangrove planting, to monster snook catches, this is hands-on conservation at its best. This two-part series kicks off with action, heart, and the kind of hope only a healthy waterway can bring. Don’t miss Part 1—where conservation meets community and everyone gets their hands wet.

programme.title: Giant 8 Point Squares Off With Decoy, 190"+ Monarch Claimed By EHD
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we join Owen Reigler in Southern Iowa as he returns to the woods after soaking in the successful hunt for the "Lochness Monster" back in early October. Returning to the famed Crabs Plot where he has seen repeated success over the years, Owen targets three mature 8 point bucks and breaks out a buck decoy to hopefully entice one into bow range. After two action packed hunts full of rare buck behavior and multiple encounters with shooters, Owen returns to the same location for the third day in a row hoping to get an opportunity at one of the three 8 points. Then, we catch up with Kaleb Greiner in Eastern Iowa who has a heartbreaking update in the chase for the Iowa monarch known as "Lucky." After finding that the giant has also fallen to the outbreak of EHD in his area, Kaleb reflects on lessons learned throughout the chase.

programme.title: Zach's Iowa Brute, Hunting A New Farm Leads To A Giant Missouri Buck On The Ground
programme.desc: We're coming at you for a second episode this week to try our very best to stay up to date with the great influx of action that the pre rut and rut has brought the team. On this episode, we kick things off with Zach Rozmus in Iowa who brings us a text book morning hunt to round out October. On top of filling his tag on an incredible brute of a buck, Zach's story showcases how working together with other hunters in your area can lead to great opportunities. Following that, we join Aidan and Avery Epperson in Missouri for a saga that brings no surprise. After acquiring permission on a new property with team member Tyler behlman on October 15th, the guys put their hunting minds to work to figure out the ground with the impending rut fast approaching. Hunting only a few times, the duo find themselves face to face with the best buck on the farm and by the end of it a tag is filled on the buck known as "Stick Tight." This is only the tip of the iceberg and with much of the month ahead of us, we're excited to continue to bring you the action as fast as we can. Next up is Mike Reed's story with the Iowa giant known as "DK" and then Drake Lamb's incredible rut hunt for a giant 8 pointer after that. Good luck hunting and thank you so much for the continued support, all of us greatly appreciate it.

programme.title: 172" River Bottom Giant Falls In The River, The Story Of Hunting "DK"
programme.desc: On this episode of Midwest Whitetail, we follow along with Mike Reed as he closes the chapter on yet another River Farm legend. Going back all the way to 2020, this buck shined as a beautiful main frame 8 with true potential to blow into a monarch. Fast forward all these years later and Mike's plan to hunt the ghostly buck finally came to fruition. Join Mike as he dives into his step by step process for hunting "DK" during the 2023 season dating back to finding the shed antler after a controlled burn in the spring. This one has it all from bucks chasing, buck vocalizations, 10 yard shots, and another recovery that saw Mike take to the river! Let us know in the comments what questions you have and as always, thank you so much for taking the time to watch another episode of Midwest Whitetail.

programme.title: Four Bucks In Three Days, Key Locations To Hunt During The Lockdown Phase
programme.desc: On this week's show we catch up with Owen Reigler in Southern Iowa who shares a few tips and strategies as gun seasons enter the fold across the country. Next, we head to Southern Illinois with Chad Holmes for a bow hunt on the day before the state's opening day of gun season. Experiencing the full force of the peak rut, Chad no sooner climbs out of his stand for the morning than hears a chase headed straight for him. The following day, his son Casen Holmes heads to a Redneck blind hoping to cash in on opening day of the Illinois firearms season. After that, we catch up with David Williams and Andy Melton who also gear up for the gun opener in Illinois. Hoping to key in on historical hot spots during the lockdown phase on their farms, the guys find themselves with back to back opportunities to fill their gun tags on two mature bucks. Looking forward, the team still has some awesome stories to share with you so be sure to stay tuned in as we move through the month of December. Thank you as always for your support!
